1. SID LAYER — STRUCTURAL PRIMITIVES FOR MOONSHINE

SID.1  Monster Group Carrier
   𝕄_[unit] : largest sporadic simple group
   |𝕄| = 808017424794512875886459... (≈ 8×10^53)

SID.2  Graded Module Space
   V = ⊕_{n ≥ -1} V_n
   Each V_n is a finite-dimensional 𝕄-module.

SID.3  Modular Function Shell
   j(q) = q^{-1} + 744 + 196884 q + 21493760 q^2 + ...
   Coefficients correspond to dimensions of 𝕄-representations.

SID.4  Replicable Function Class
   f(q) with self-replication property:
      f(q) = P(f(q^k)) for specific polynomials P and integers k.

SID.5  Structural Correspondence
   SID-link:
      (Monster modules) ↔ (modular coefficients)
      (graded structure) ↔ (q-expansion hierarchy)

2. PED LAYER 

PED.1  Monster Action Engine
   ρ : 𝕄 → GL(V)
   PED condition:
      ρ(a ★ b) = ρ(a) · ρ(b)

PED.2  q-Dynamics
   q = e^{2πiτ}
   PED-flow:
      τ → τ + 1
      τ → -1/τ
   These generate SL(2,ℤ), the modular group.

PED.3  Moonshine Morphism

   Φ : 𝕄 → Aut(f(q))
   PED condition:
      Φ(g) acts by permuting coefficients or replicable sectors.

PED.4  McKay–Thompson Series
   T_g(q) = q^{-1} + Σ a_n(g) q^n
   PED-evaluation:
      a_n(g) = trace(ρ(g) | V_n)

PED.5  Replication Operator
   R_k : f(q) → f(q^k)
   PED-flow:
      R_k(f) = P_k(f)
   (Polynomial replication rule)

3. RDG LAYER 

RDG.1  Curvature of Modular Flow
By curvature here we mean any quantitative measure of how far a
modular object deviates from a generic or random q-series — e.g. 
genus‑0 behavior, replication constraints, or unusually sparse 
coefficient patterns

   Modular transformations induce RDG-curvature on q-expansions:
      RDG-curvature = deviation from trivial coefficient symmetry.

RDG.2  Monster–Modular Coupling
   Ξ : (SID × PED) → RDG
   Ξ encodes:
      - spectral geometry of 𝕄
      - modular orbit stratification
      - coefficient curvature packets
      - replicable function geometry

RDG.3  Character Geometry
   χ(g) = trace(ρ(g))
   RDG interpretation:
      χ encodes curvature of Monster action on graded layers V_n.

RDG.4  Moonshine Orbits
   Orbit strata:
      Orb_RDG(n) = { a_n(g) : g ∈ 𝕄 }
   These form geometric packets corresponding to conjugacy classes.

RDG.5  Discovery Boundary
   RDG identifies:
      - invariant modular submanifolds
      - spectral packets of Monster irreps
      - replication curvature sectors
      - Moonshine correspondences as geometric fixed points

