5. RELATIONAL GEOMETRY
   The modular geometry of T_g(q) reveals the Moonshine
   correspondence as a geometric fixed point of the Monster–modular
   coupling.

Curvature signal:
   T_g(q) is a Hauptmodul for Γ0(p)^+
   (genus-0 modular curve)

Orbit strata:
   Orb_RDG(n) = { a_n(h) : h ∈ conj(g) }
   Coefficient packets align with Monster conjugacy classes.

Character geometry:
   χ_n(g) = a_n(g)
   Encodes spectral curvature of g acting on V_n.

Discovery boundary:
   Fixed-point condition:
      (SID × PED) → RDG
      yields genus-0 Moonshine correspondence for g.

